Sentence: This book belongs to myself.
This : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "book"
book : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "belongs"
belongs : verb "belong", 3rd person singular, present tense, active voice
to : preposition, introduces the indirect object
myself : reflexive pronoun, first person singular, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: That car was driven by himself.
That : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "car"
car : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "was driven"
was : auxiliary verb "be", past tense, passive voice
driven : past participle of "drive", part of the passive verb phrase
by : preposition, introduces the agent in passive voice
himself : reflexive pronoun, third person masculine singular, object of the preposition "by"

Sentence: These cookies were baked by ourselves.
These : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "cookies"
cookies : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "were baked"
were : auxiliary verb "be", past tense, plural, passive voice
baked : past participle of "bake", part of the passive verb phrase
by : preposition, introduces the agent in passive voice
ourselves : reflexive pronoun, first person plural, object of the preposition "by"

Sentence: Those students taught themselves the lesson.
Those : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "students"
students : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "taught"
taught : verb "teach", past tense, active voice
themselves : reflexive pronoun, third person plural, indirect object of "taught"
the : definite article, modifies "lesson"
lesson : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "taught"

Sentence: I made this cake for myself.
I : personal pronoun, first person singular, subject of the verb "made"
made : verb "make", past tense, active voice
this : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "cake"
cake : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "made"
for : preposition, indicates beneficiary
myself : reflexive pronoun, first person singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: She blamed herself for that mistake.
She : personal pronoun, third person feminine singular, subject of the verb "blamed"
blamed : verb "blame", past tense, active voice
herself : reflexive pronoun, third person feminine singular, direct object of "blamed"
for : preposition, indicates reason
that : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "mistake"
mistake : common noun, singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: You should prepare yourself for these challenges.
You : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "should prepare"
should : modal auxiliary verb, indicates obligation
prepare : main verb, base form, active voice
yourself : reflexive pronoun, second person singular, direct object of "prepare"
for : preposition, indicates purpose or target
these : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "challenges"
challenges : common noun, plural, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: They built those houses themselves.
They : personal pronoun, third person plural, subject of the verb "built"
built : verb "build", past tense, active voice
those : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "houses"
houses : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "built"
themselves : reflexive pronoun, third person plural, emphatic use modifying "They"

Sentence: He bought this ticket for himself.
He : personal pronoun, third person masculine singular, subject of the verb "bought"
bought : verb "buy", past tense, active voice
this : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "ticket"
ticket : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "bought"
for : preposition, indicates beneficiary
himself : reflexive pronoun, third person masculine singular, object of the preposition "for"

Sentence: We painted these walls by ourselves.
We : personal pronoun, first person plural, subject of the verb "painted"
painted : verb "paint", past tense, active voice
these : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "walls"
walls : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "painted"
by : preposition, part of the idiomatic phrase "by ourselves"
ourselves : reflexive pronoun, first person plural, emphasizes independent action

Sentence: Did you see that bird over there by itself?
Did : auxiliary verb "do", past tense, used for question formation
you : personal pronoun, second person, subject of the verb "see"
see : main verb, base form, active voice
that : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "bird"
bird : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "see"
over : adverb, part of the phrasal adverb "over there"
there : adverb, indicates location
by : preposition, indicates state of being alone
itself : reflexive pronoun, third person neuter singular, object of the preposition "by"

Sentence: The manager assigned those tasks to herself.
The : definite article, modifies "manager"
manager : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "assigned"
assigned : verb "assign", past tense, active voice
those : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "tasks"
tasks : common noun, plural, direct object of the verb "assigned"
to : preposition, introduces the recipient
herself : reflexive pronoun, third person feminine singular, object of the preposition "to"

Sentence: Please fix this computer yourself.
Please : interjection, used to make a polite request
fix : verb, base form, imperative mood, active voice
this : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "computer"
computer : common noun, singular, direct object of the verb "fix"
yourself : reflexive pronoun, second person singular, emphatic use modifying the implied subject "you"

Sentence: Those children entertained themselves all afternoon.
Those : demonstrative determiner, plural, modifies "children"
children : common noun, plural, subject of the verb "entertained"
entertained : verb "entertain", past tense, active voice
themselves : reflexive pronoun, third person plural, direct object of "entertained"
all : determiner, modifies "afternoon"
afternoon : common noun, singular, adverbial of time

Sentence: Is this seat taken by yourself?
Is : auxiliary verb "be", present tense, used for question formation and passive voice
this : demonstrative determiner, singular, modifies "seat"
seat : common noun, singular, subject of the verb "is taken"
taken : past participle of "take", part of the passive verb phrase
by : preposition, introduces the agent in passive voice
yourself : reflexive pronoun, second person singular, object of the preposition "by"
